Dune: Part Two makes it abundantly clear that these four are the future of Hollywood, each with different strengths but an overall high level of skill and screen presence. If the “movie star” is still a thing (and, well, debatable imo), Chalamet, Zendaya, Butler, and Pugh are it. https://t.co/sNBpjwMBgj

So yeah, just watched #DunePartTwo, and I’m in awe, as if abducted by a sand worm, not just by the visual and artistic brilliancy, but by how layered this movie managed to be over the complexities of politics, religion and faith! The definitive cinematic sci-fi apotheosis!

#DenisVilleneuve delivered a masterwork so richly crafted that it’s indeed set a new bar, so high, to the sci-fi and fantasy genres that might take a generation until we see someone else rising to the challenge.

I remember when I first saw the #StarWars prequels and how mesmerised I was by the politics of it all, as simple as they were.

Little I know that one day we would have a movie like #DunePartTwo. It’s almost like you watching Suits growing up and then watching Succession 3 decades later.

Denis managed to deliver Political machinations and Religion manipulation as pure and complex as they are. Not vilifying, glorifying or taking sides, because as #BeneGesserit Reverend Mother says, there are no sides, really.

And technically, #DunePartTwo is as wondrous as its plot. The scale, and the breathtaking imagery are unparalleled, the wide shots at the third act when chaos breaks lose give us the notion of the grandeur of those places and those spaceships.

And the set and props designs? What about those ships that looked like Brainiac brought to life? I was living for that all. The world building is insane, and much grander and deeper than we ever saw in part one. Many people comparing it to #TheTwoTowers & other films. I would add #GameOfThrones Seasons 5 & 6.

The stunt work, with incredible fight choreographies, battle organisation & development gave veracity and stakes to everything. The way they were shot and the incredible editing work made every scene feel larger, richer & high stakes.

And it has the best ensemble cast work I’ve seen. The chemistry between them all and how everyone is giving their A-game is just insane, specially in a world so vast as this. Even the smaller parts leave their deep marks, in this movie there are no small parts, because there are no small actors here. 
Love them all, but I need to give shout outs to:

#TimothéeChalamet blew me away. There are 3 scenes towards the end you won’t see them coming, it’s just a transfiguration before your eyes, voice and body wise!

#Zendaya for the first time made me feel like she is a on-screen movie star. The way she dominates every frame she’s in, and how she can say so much just with her eyes was just a delight to see.

#RebeccaFerguson was threateningly terrific. I think it’s her best work ever, specially when she goes full intergalactic Karen.

#DaveBautista made me feel so emotional and proud to see how far he has come as an actor. I feel genuinely so happy for him.

#AustinButler was brutal. I thought he couldn’t be any better than in #TheBikeriders but that’s nothing compared to the level up he gave himself with #FeydRauthaHarkonnen. It’s Ledger’s #Joker level!

And the sound! OMG the sound work in this entry goes even further, you have no idea how much more it enhances everything.

To summarise, #DunePartTwo is the new definition of what a full cinematic experience is and what cinema can achieve, giving us an engaging story that challenges you, makes you think and stays with you - and might stay in the collective moviegoing zeitgeist forever - never afraid of going the extra mile, never underestimating the audiences’ capacity of absorbing it all.
All of that enveloped by technical mastery very rare these days. 

#DunePartTwo is basically the apotheosis of the cinematic experience,  as a big celebration of what cinema is and can be and can deliver, as rich, religiously divine and artistic and smart and visceral as it can possibly be.

Long live the fighters! Long live the cinema and the ones who still have faith in cinema, because once in a generation we get our own version of Muad'Dib to lead us to a cinematic paradise full of green & wonder!
LISAN AL DENIS VILLENEUVE GAIB!
